definitions.definition: To perform or create a speedrun .
examples: In my most recent attempt to speedrun this game, I almost managed to beat the world record.

definitions.definition: To do something or undergo some process as quickly as possible.
examples: John decided to speedrun his trip to the grocery store.

main_definition: ( ambitransitive ) To perform or create a speedrun .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension , Internet slang ) To do something or undergo some process as quickly as possible.
